Extracted Variables:
- x1: Number of regular tacos made
- x2: Number of deluxe tacos made

Definitions:
- x1, x2 >= 0

Constraints:
- x1 \leq 50 (demand for regular tacos)
- x2 \leq 40 (demand for deluxe tacos)
- x1 + x2 \leq 70 (total number of tacos that can be made)

Objective:
- Maximize profit: Z = 2.50x1 + 3.55x2
